### CHAPTER LXXXII.

1\. The eighty-second subject is this, that, when thou risest up from
the bed-clothes, it is necessary to tie the *sacred thread-*girdle <span
id="fr_1523"></span>[3](#fn_1512.md) again *at* that same place, and it is
not desirable to put *forth* a step without the girdle.

2\. For it is declared in revelation, that every single step which *one*
puts forth without the *sacred thread-*girdle is a Farmân sin <span
id="fr_1524"></span>[4](#fn_1513.md), *and* through four steps it becomes a
Tanâvar sin which would be a weight of a thousand *and* two hundred
dirhams <span id="fr_1525"></span>[5](#fn_1514.md). 3. Therefore, it is
necessary to keep watch *over* oneself, as regards this sin, and to tie
on the *sacred thread-*girdle.

